title: Prigozhin buried without fanfare after spectacular fall from grace
description: From alpha to omega, Yevgeny Prigozhin has ended life as it began.

title: Man could face death penalty over alleged 'aggravated homosexuality'
description: A man is the first in Uganda to be charged with alleged "aggravated homosexuality", and could face the death penalty if convicted.

title: State of emergency declared as Florida prepares for life-threatening hurricane
description: Residents of Florida's Gulf Coast have been warned of a risk of life-threatening storm surges and dangerous hurricane-force winds over the next two days as Hurricane Idalia hurtles towards the state.

title: Pakistani ex-cricketer 'offered money to kill' Dutch politician
description: Dutch prosecutors have demanded a 12-year prison sentence if a former Pakistani cricketer is found guilty of incitement to murder anti-Islam Dutch politician Geert Wilders.

title: International appeal to identify child's body found in German river
description: An international appeal is under way to identify the body of a boy found weighed down with a flagstone slab and wrapped in foil in the River Danube in Germany.

title: Raging Greek wildfire is biggest recorded in the EU in 23 years
description: Firefighters in Greece continue to battle what has become the biggest wildfire in the EU since record-keeping began.

title: Ukraine says Russia is 'sinking ships' to protect Crimean bridge – here's what we found
description: Russia has "sunk" a number of vessels by the Crimean bridge using what analysts call a "200-year-old strategy" to defend itself against the emerging threat of Ukrainian sea drones.

title: Cleverly will be walking a tightrope during China visit - but he is already behind the curve
description: As he lands in Beijing, the first British foreign secretary to do so in five years, James Cleverly, faces the same challenge that has perplexed visiting diplomats for decades.

title: Wagner boss Prigozhin 'buried privately in St Petersburg cemetery'
description: Wagner mercenary boss Yevgeny Prigozhin has been buried privately in a "farewell ceremony" in a St Petersburg cemetery, according to his press team.

title: Voice assistants Siri-ously lacking when asked for instructions on giving CPR
description: Voice assistants have become a crucial part of our lives - giving us the weather forecast, playing music on demand, and even helping us cheat at pub quizzes.

title: 'Oh my gosh': Tennis player complains of 'weed' smell during US Open match
description: A top-10 tennis player said she could smell "weed" on court during her US Open match before suffering a shock defeat.

title: Cash 'reward' offered to newlywed couples if bride is young enough
description: A county in China is offering newlywed couples a "reward" of 1,000 yuan (£109) if the bride is aged 25 and under, as the country battles a declining birth rate and searches for ways to get young people to marry.

title: Why can't passengers get off a plane stuck on the tarmac?
description: Picture the scene - you've boarded your plane, buckled your seatbelt and switched your phone to flight mode.

title: Leaked 'secret' meeting between Israel and Libya sparks riots in Tripoli
description: The White House is reportedly "furious" with the Israeli government after they publicised a meeting between Israeli and Libyan foreign ministers.

title: Imran Khan's corruption conviction and three-year jail term suspended
description: A corruption conviction against Imran Khan has been suspended - with his three-year jail term overturned.
